name: PhysicalAddress
label: physical address
definition: physical address where communications can be addressed, papers served or representatives located for any kind of organization or person

name: Address
definition: index to a location to which communications may be delivered
label: address

name: PhysicalAddressingScheme
label: physical addressing scheme
definition: scheme for specifying physical addresses according to a country specific standard

name: AddressingScheme
label: addressing scheme
definition: system for allocating addresses to objects

name: Postcode
label: postcode
definition: sequence of characters used to assist in the sorting of mail

name: PostOfficeBoxAddress
definition: physical address used to deliver communications to a designated container at a local post office or the local equivalent for the jurisdiction, where mail is held until the recipient collects it, rather than to a given house, building, or other location
label: post office box address

name: StreetSuffix
definition: classifier for a street or other delivery location, such as a dwelling located along a waterway
explanatoryNote: The suffix may provide some insight into the size or length of the street, though not necessarily consistently. In some cities, the suffix differentiates the street from another in the same context, such as 19th Street vs. 19th Avenue in San Francisco.
label: street suffix

name: AddressComponent
label: address component
definition: aspect of an address

name: SecondaryUnitIndicator
definition: index to the specific unit within a secondary unit, such as a building or apartment, at a particular street address
label: secondary unit indicator

name: ConventionalStreetAddress
explanatoryNote: Other unconventional addresses may include rural and highway route addresses, general delivery addresses, post office box addresses, private mail center addresses, and so forth.
label: conventional street address
definition: physical address that identifies a location on a street to which communications may be delivered

name: GeographicDirectionalSymbol
label: geographic directional symbol
definition: code element that gives directional information for postal delivery

name: RegionSpecificIdentifier
label: region-specific identifier
definition: geographic region or subdivision identifier used internally by a country or other region

name: StreetAddress
definition: index to a location that consists of a primary address number, predirectional, street name, suffix, postdirectional, and an optional secondary unit
label: street address

name: SupplementalAddressUnit
definition: address component that includes a specific route, box, apartment, condominium or other indicator or unit associated with a specific address
label: supplemental address unit

name: PostOfficeBox
definition: post office box associated with an address
label: post office box
explanatoryNote: Post office box identifiers are only unique to a given jurisdiction, which may be a post office, town, or other region.

name: SupplementalAddressComponent
explanatoryNote: Supplemental components include post office box information, rural route and highway contract route information, private mailboxes, and so forth, that are not part of a conventional street address.
label: supplemental address component
definition: address component that provides additional information that is important to ensuring proper delivery of communications

name: PhysicalAddressIdentifier
label: physical address identifier
definition: unique identifier for a physical address

name: PostCodeArea
label: post code area
definition: physical area uniquely identified by some postal code

name: PostdirectionalSymbol
definition: geographic directional symbol that follows the street name and street suffix in a street address
label: postdirectional symbol

name: StreetName
label: street name
definition: identifier for a street in some context (e.g., city, municipality, geographic region)

name: PrimaryAddressNumber
explanatoryNote: Although traditionally called a 'number', the street number may consist of alphanumeric characters, for example, '221B'.
definition: address component that identifies a location with respect to a given street
label: primary address number

name: PostOfficeBoxDesignator
definition: designator used, together with an identifier, for a post office box
label: post office box designator

name: SupplementalAddressDesignator
definition: classifier for supplemental address information, such as a highway contract route, rural route, building complex, shopping center, condominium complex, mail box, or other similar designation
label: supplemental address designator

name: StructureName
label: structure name
definition: name for a building, house, office complex, shopping center, or other structure or group of structures

name: SecondaryUnit
label: secondary unit
definition: address component that identifies an individual unit within a larger structure, such as an apartment, office, hangar, slip, mailbox, and so forth, at a given street address

name: VirtualAddress
definition: address identifying a virtual, i.e. non-physical, location
label: virtual address

name: PredirectionalSymbol
definition: geographic directional symbol that occurs after the primary street number but before the street name in a street address
label: predirectional symbol

name: SecondaryUnitDesignator
label: secondary unit designator
definition: classifier for a smaller structure or component within a larger facility, such as an apartment, office, mail stop, or other similar designation
explanatoryNote: Note that only certain secondary units require a secondary range, such as an apartment number, to complete a delivery point.

name: Space
definition: extent set apart or available, such as a parking or storage space
label: space

name: hasPostdirectionalSymbol
label: has postdirectional symbol
definition: specifies a geographic directional symbol that follows the street name and street suffix in a street address

name: requiresSecondaryUnitRange
definition: if true, indicates that an additional qualifier is needed to complete the delivery point description, such as an apartment number
label: requires secondary unit range
explanatoryNote: Note that in some cases, such as for lobby or office, if there are multiple secondary units then a range may be needed to differentiate between them, even if the range is not always required.

name: hasAttentionLine
label: has attention line
definition: an optional, free text address line denoting the intended recipient

name: Penthouse
definition: structure or dwelling on the roof or top floor of a building
label: penthouse

name: Key
label: key
definition: usually metal instrument by which the bolt of a lock is turned

name: Stop
definition: stopping place, such as a bus or mail stop
label: stop

name: Department
definition: division of a large organization such as a government, university, business, or shop, dealing with a specific subject, commodity, or area of activity
label: department

name: Lobby
definition: entrance hall, corridor, or vestibule, as in a public building, often serving as an anteroom; foyer
label: lobby

name: Unit
definition: area in a facility, such as a medical facility or hospital that is specially staffed and equipped to provide a particular service or type of care
label: unit

name: hasMailRouting
definition: an optional, free text address line containing explicit routing information (this elements's presence indicates that this address is a routing / 'care of' address)
label: has mail routing

name: Pier
definition: structure extending into navigable water for use as a landing place or promenade
label: pier

name: Office
definition: place where a particular kind of business is transacted or a service is supplied
label: office

name: Rear
definition: side or part of a building at the back, located opposite its front
label: rear

name: Basement
label: basement
definition: part of a building consisting of rooms that are partly or entirely below ground

name: Side
definition: place, space, or direction with respect to a center or to a line of division
label: side

name: Trailer
label: trailer
definition: vehicle designed to serve wherever parked as a temporary dwelling or place of business

name: Building
label: building
definition: relatively permanent enclosed structure, that has a roof and walls and stands more or less permanently in one place

name: Lot
definition: measured parcel of land having fixed boundaries and designated on a plot or survey
label: lot

name: hasAddressLine2
label: has address line 2
definition: the second line of the street address

name: Floor
label: floor
explanatoryNote: Labeling systems for floors vary from country to country, and may be specific to the building, for example, whether or not a 13th floor is identified as such tends to be on a case-by-case basis.
definition: all of the rooms or areas on the same level of a building; a story

name: hasSecondaryUnit
definition: specifies an individual unit within a larger structure, such as an apartment, office, hangar, slip, mailbox, and so forth, at a given street address
label: has secondary unit

name: hasStreetName
definition: specifies an identifier for a street in some context (e.g., 'Baker', 'First', 'Main')
label: has street name

name: hasIndividualPostcode
definition: indicates the local or international postcode element of a delivery address as specified by the local postal service
label: has individual postcode

name: Apartment
definition: room or a group of related rooms, among similar sets in one building, designed for use as a dwelling
label: apartment

name: Suite
definition: group of rooms occupied as a unit
label: suite

name: hasStreetAddress
definition: indicates a fully-specified address component that consists of a primary address number, predirectional, street name, suffix, postdirectional, and an optional secondary unit
label: has street address

name: hasTransliteratedAddress
definition: identifies a transliterated (i.e., in Latin or Romanized ASCII) address for the registered entity
label: has transliterated address

name: hasPostalCode
definition: the postal code of this address as specified by the local postal service
label: has postal code

name: Slip
definition: sloping ramp extending out into the water to serve as a place for landing or repairing ships; ship's or boat's berth between two piers
label: slip

name: hasAddressLine1
label: has address line 1
definition: the first line of the street address

name: Room
label: room
definition: partitioned part of the inside of a building

name: Lower
definition: floor of a building in a multistory structure that is closer to ground level
label: lower

name: hasPrimaryAddressNumber
definition: specifies a a location with respect to a given street
label: has primary address number

name: Hangar
label: hanger
definition: shed or shelter; any relatively wide structure used for housing airplanes or airships

name: Upper
definition: floor of a building in a multistory structure that is farther away from the ground level
label: upper

name: hasAddressLine3
definition: the third line of the street address
label: has address line 3

name: hasStructureName
definition: specifies an identifier for a building, house, office complex, shopping center, or other structure or group of structures
label: has structure name

name: hasAddress
definition: indicates a means by which something (in the case of a network address) or some entity may be located or contacted or may receive correspondence
label: has address

name: hasStreetSuffix
label: has street suffix
definition: specifies an additional qualifier for a street or other delivery location, such as a dwelling located along a waterway

name: hasPredirectionalSymbol
label: has predirectional symbol
definition: specifies a geographic directional symbol that occurs after the primary street number but before the street name in a street address

name: Front
definition: side or part of a building that presents itself to view first, that faces the street; the most forward part of a building
label: front
